        <trans-unit id="175" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>How is depreciation calculated using the equally divided depreciation method if the asset calendar is changed during the asset life cycle?</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="176" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>When Finance and Operations calculates depreciation by using the equally divided depreciation method, the calculation is based on the fiscal calendar that is selected in the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Calendar<ept id="p1">**</ept> field on the <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>Books<ept id="p2">**</ept> page.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="177" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>If an asset calendar is changed during the asset life cycle, the number of fiscal periods, such as months or quarters, in a fiscal year is calculated based on the current calendar.</source>
